# Figure 8B-Morphometric Analysis of Alveolar Architecture

Mean alveolar wall distances were quantified from histological lung sections to assess differences in alveolar structure across developmental and BPD groups.

## Workflow

- Histological lung sections were imaged using brightfield microscopy.
- Multiple representative regions of interest (ROIs) were selected from each donor.
- Images were imported into ImageJ/Fiji and calibrated using the image scale.
- Alveolar wall distances were measured using the ImageJ line measurement tool.
- Measurements were averaged across ROIs for each donor.
- Group comparisons and statistical analyses were performed using GraphPad Prism.

## Input Data

- PT-NB lung sections
- FT-NB lung sections
- BPD lung sections
- Multiple ROIs per donor

## Output

- Mean alveolar wall distance measurements
- Group-wise comparisons of alveolar architecture

## Software

- ImageJ/Fiji
- GraphPad Prism
